  "prompt": "What is the best WYSIWYG editor for Drupal 7?",
  "response": "For Drupal 7, some of the most recommended WYSIWYG editors include:\n\n1. **CKEditor**: This is one of the most popular WYSIWYG editors for Drupal. It provides a rich text editing experience, is user-friendly, and offers a wide range of features and plugins to extend functionality.\n\n2. **TinyMCE**: Another widely-used WYSIWYG editor, TinyMCE is lightweight and customizable. It also has a good number of plugins and configurations available to tailor it to your needs.\n\n3. **markup**: This is a simple WYSIWYG editor that provides basic text editing capabilities without being overly complex, making it a good choice for users who need straightforward functionality.\n\nTo use these editors in Drupal 7, you can install the respective modules (such as the CKEditor or TinyMCE modules) and configure them according to your requirements. Both CKEditor and TinyMCE offer good support, frequent updates, and a community of users, making them reliable choices for a WYSIWYG editor in Drupal 7.",
